<title>SRI LANKA: Sri Lanka forex market closed for Buddhist holiday.</title>
<headline>Sri Lanka forex market closed for Buddhist holiday.</headline>
<dateline>COLOMBO 1997-05-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Sri Lanka's foreign exchange market was closed for trading on Thursday because of a Buddhist religious holiday.</p>
<p>The Sri Lankan rupee closed stronger at 58.42 to the dollar on Tuesday, when the market was last open, mainly on lack of demand from importers and the greenback's overseas weakness.</p>
<p>Trading will resume on Friday.</p>
